Subject: 6th Annual High Country Bus Festival - update

WOW - just 2 more weeks until HCBF 6 !!!!!!!!!!!

dates of festival:  July 26, 27, and 28th  2002.
main webpage:  http://www.mindspring.com/~contecmidwest/index.html


- POT LUCK/Chicken Wing Cook-Off:   Make em' hot, make em' not just make em! 
  Submit your special recipe to the panel of judges.  We will also have a 
POT LUCK SUPPER:  If your not cooking Wings - Please bring any dish or 
anything that would go well with wings - celery, chips, bread, veggies, etc. 
There will be a lot of people so we'll all need to pitch in to feed the 
masses.

- Full Moon Bus Club Breakfast Burritos:  NEED I SAY MORE  :-) :-)  click 
the link to goto the "grocery list" and see what you can bring to help us 
feed to group......"what we have in mind is breakfast in bed for two hundred 
thousand......"
http://www.mindspring.com/~contecmidwest/page7.html

- TYPE 2 Raffle:   We will hold a raffle to raise money for the TYPE 2 LIST. 
  There will be some super prizes......thanks to our sponsors: Bus Depot, 
Eurocampers and McGuires to name a few!  Special thanks to Rod "calander" 
and Wild Bill for helping to run the raffle.  There will also be a 50/50 
raffle with proceeds going to the Full Moon Bus Club.

- Tech Class:  Steve Dolan and Marc Derring will be holding a workshop on 
Saturday at 11:00am.  Topics covered will be:  setting timing, carb 
adjustments, and more!  You won't want to miss this workshop from our 
resident Bus Guru's.

-  CARABUS:   If you want to lead or get into a carabus from your area to 
HCBF, check out the webpage to see if anyone from your area is leading a 
group, if not, then sign up to lead a carbus yourself:
http://www.mindspring.com/~contecmidwest/page7.html

- VW FAMILY FEUD:  I sent out the survey to the list last week, and would 
like to thank those who responded.  But, we only received 40 responses and 
we need at least 100 bus owners to survey!  Please do not re-submit you 
answers, but if you did not submit your survey last week please click this 
link and follow the instructions:
http://www.mindspring.com/~contecmidwest/page8.html

Schedule of Events:   We now have 2 bands scheduled for Saturday along with 
the tech class and the VW Family Feud.  Check the schedule page for all the 
latest information:
http://www.mindspring.com/~contecmidwest/page7.html

email me off list if you have any other questions......

GO BUS GO  - all the way to Boone!
Buddah




The Sixth Annual High Country Bus Festival
July 26-28 2002    near Boone, NC

http://www.mindspring.com/~contecmidwest

"GoBusGo"


